===== audit-map/25-accounts-routing/account-status.md =====
# Account Status

## Verified Current State

- Native Codex CLI: logged in via ChatGPT
- Arctic global store: installed, with authenticated `codex`, `google`, `github-copilot`, and `antigravity`
- Arctic slot-isolation framework: ready
- All six Arctic `codex-*` slots: authenticated and model-verified with preferred model `gpt-5.4`
- Arctic `google-main`: authenticated and model-verified with preferred model `gemini-3.1-pro-preview`
- Both Arctic GitHub Copilot slots: authenticated and model-verified with preferred model `gpt-5.4`
- Arctic `antigravity-main`: authenticated and model-verified with preferred model `claude-opus-4-5-thinking`
- Arctic execution smoke across all six `codex-*` slots: `verified` on `gpt-5.3-codex`
- Arctic execution smoke on `google-main`: `verified`
- Arctic execution smoke across both GitHub Copilot slots using visible `gpt-5.4`: `failed`
- Arctic execution smoke on `copilot-raed2180416` with `github-copilot/gemini-3.1-pro-preview`: `verified`
- Arctic execution smoke on `copilot-raed2180416` with `github-copilot/gpt-4.1`: `verified`
- Arctic execution smoke on `copilot-accneww432` with `github-copilot/gemini-3.1-pro-preview`: `verified`
- Arctic execution smoke on both GitHub Copilot slots with `github-copilot/gpt-5.3-codex`: `verified`
- Caveman: installed as global skills under `~/.agents/skills/`

## Safe Interpretation

- Native Codex is ready now.
- Arctic account continuity is structurally configured through isolated slots.
- Arctic login is complete for the requested slots.
- Arctic model visibility is complete for the requested slots.
- Arctic Codex execution is now proven across all six slots at the pinned fallback model `gpt-5.3-codex`.
- Arctic Google execution is proven through `google-main`.
- Arctic GitHub Copilot execution is now promoted on both slots through `github-copilot/gpt-5.3-codex`, while visible `gpt-5.4` still fails as `model_not_supported`.
- Arctic Antigravity is now integrated into the slot framework and model discovery, but it does not expose a `gpt-5.3-codex` or `gpt-5.4` class route in this environment.
- Arctic-visible higher tiers such as Codex `gpt-5.4` / `gpt-5.4-mini` remain discovery-only until separately execution-verified.
- High-stakes audit passes now prefer native Codex first, but can continue on execution-verified alternates when native is cooling down.
- Caveman is available as an optional skill layer, not as an always-on system behavior.

## Plain-English Readiness

- local audit OS: ready
- native Codex execution: ready
- Arctic slot-aware multi-account routing: authenticated, with six Codex slots, Google, both Copilot slots, and one Antigravity slot discovered; execution-verified alternates currently include Codex, Google, and Copilot pinned runtime models
- Caveman deterministic per-pass policy: ready
- Caveman deterministic skill auto-application: not yet verified

## Intended Slots

Use `25-accounts-routing/desired-provider-account-plan.md` as the current slot map.

Operational status after login can be listed with:

- `bash audit-map/16-scripts/arctic-slot-status.sh`
- `25-accounts-routing/current-model-availability.md`

