The proof-risk wrapper is clearly unsafe for blind live use. It doesn’t just inspect; it can create imports, validate/review/approve them, recompute risk, create proof runs, and then activate semesters. The only conditionally reversible part is the semester activation, and that’s nested inside a larger prewarm path that can mutate live state before any restore. I’m checking the teaching-parity implementation next to see whether it inherits that risk.
